Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.87,0:00:08.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All of the various economic
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.44,0:00:10.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,powers are hastily preparing \Nto launch their forces.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.66,0:00:15.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.12,0:00:21.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,These AHSMB units will \Nbe our primary fighters!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.30,0:00:23.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Make sure they're in tip-top shape!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.21,0:00:24.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, Boss!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.10,0:00:24.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Got it!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.72,0:00:29.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Our fleets against \Ntheirs? Sounds exciting!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.80,0:00:31.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Accurate instructions are a must to
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.59,0:00:33.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,keep our allies from \Nfalling into disarray.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.27,0:00:35.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're always so uptight!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.49,0:00:37.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You'll never get anywhere like that...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.57,0:00:39.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,with the enemy or women.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.60,0:00:41.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you have time for idle chatter,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.43,0:00:43.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,work on memorizing the \Nenemy's formations!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.86,0:00:45.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.82,0:00:48.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have no idea what to \Nexpect from the Wulgaru.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.45,0:00:50.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After all, they consider this "hunting".
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.79,0:00:52.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We need be prepared for an attack
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.33,0:00:54.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,if they strike while we're on the move.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.42,0:00:56.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come what may, our \Nprimary goal is to reach
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.90,0:00:58.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the gate in one piece.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.42,0:00:59.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.67,0:01:03.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But how will we power the \Ngate-destroying Straggle Laser?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.22,0:01:05.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Weren't the flagships \Nfrom the economic powers
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.94,0:01:07.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,supposed to supply the power?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.37,0:01:08.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's the plan,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.78,0:01:11.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but the charge time upon reaching \Nthe gate takes too long.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.23,0:01:15.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If the enemy opened fire, they'd \Nhave no choice but to sit it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.73,0:01:20.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're making Izuru participate \Nin this operation?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.61,0:01:25.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As his primary physician, \NI can't permit this.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.82,0:01:27.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I understand,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.48,0:01:30.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but the fate of Earth rests on \Nthe success of this operation.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.66,0:01:34.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am aware of the position \Nyou're in, but I am a doctor!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.75,0:01:36.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It is my job to protect my patients.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.91,0:03:13.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You still haven't been discharged \Nfrom the hospital, have you?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.94,0:03:16.37,Ep Title,,0000,0000,0000,,"Night before the Decisive Battle"
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.64,0:03:15.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have to participate in this operation!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.89,0:03:17.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stay and get your rest!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.39,0:03:21.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wow! Just now, didn't you \Nsound kinda big brother-ish?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.15,0:03:24.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Izuru!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.90,0:03:26.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, no! You're supposed to take it easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.94,0:03:28.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You should stop him, Asagi!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.38,0:03:29.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm trying to!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.28,0:03:31.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yep! Big Brother hasn't \Ndone anything wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.82,0:03:34.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've already told you, \Nstop calling me that!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.29,0:03:35.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? What's the big deal?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.28,0:03:39.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We merely inherited DNA \Nfrom the same human.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.08,0:03:41.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And it feels weird for him to \Nsuddenly start calling me that...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.17,0:03:45.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But it doesn't change the fact that \Nyou're Izuru's brother, does it?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.99,0:03:47.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I should have kept this to myself...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.64,0:03:50.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm kinda jealous! You've got a brother!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.97,0:03:54.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In that case, Suruga, you're \Nfree to call me "Big Bro".
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.08,0:03:55.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No freaking way!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.14,0:03:59.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But isn't everyone here \Nsorta like family?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.90,0:04:02.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's how I think of you guys.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.24,0:04:04.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tamaki...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.77,0:04:06.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Asagi is my big brother,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.94,0:04:08.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Izuru is my little brother,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.65,0:04:11.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and I guess Kei is like my mom!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.56,0:04:13.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who are you calling a mom?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.95,0:04:13.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}What 'bout me? Well? Well?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.70,0:04:16.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Commander Simon!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.12,0:04:22.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Izuru Hitachi, I need \Nto have a word with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.04,0:04:26.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, we'd better be going.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.06,0:04:32.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Izuru Hitachi, submit your \Nresignation papers immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.23,0:04:33.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that clear?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.30,0:04:35.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A moment, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.08,0:04:38.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That was an order!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.18,0:04:39.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am going to fight!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.23,0:04:40.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not happening.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.98,0:04:41.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why not?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.38,0:04:46.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In your current condition, you \Ncould jeopardize the operation.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.01,0:04:47.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll do my best to see that I don't!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.03,0:04:50.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Waiting for everyone alone \Nat a safe distance...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.19,0:04:52.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That would be far harder on me!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.41,0:04:55.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've fought along their \Nsides this whole time!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.66,0:04:56.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.01,0:05:06.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if... piloting an AHSMB \Nagain could prove fatal?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.34,0:05:15.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We were born for the \Nsole purpose to fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.14,0:05:16.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's what we were raised to do;
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.80,0:05:18.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,why our memories were erased.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.31,0:05:20.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But... But despite all \Nof that, I made friends
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.75,0:05:22.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and had some fun times.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.33,0:05:25.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So I want to be with everyone!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.60,0:05:28.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If they are out there fighting, \Nthen I want to fight, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.20,0:05:39.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will grant you permission \Nto board the Godinion.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.05,0:05:45.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.39,0:06:01.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will fight with all of my might,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.85,0:06:04.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so that Izuru doesn't have \Nto enter the frontlines.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.90,0:06:07.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will protect him!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.06,0:06:12.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Izuru is my friend... as \Nwell as my little brother!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.15,0:06:18.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Uh, I'm still the only one who \Nknows about our DNA donors.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.62,0:06:20.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.80,0:06:29.49,OS,,0000,0000,0000,,COMPOSURE
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.49,0:06:30.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Welcome back!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.79,0:06:31.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Everything okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.96,0:06:32.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.71,0:06:33.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What about Izuru?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.76,0:06:35.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He'll be able to board the Godinion.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.84,0:06:36.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is he all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.47,0:06:41.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ange, have you finished \Nyour medical exams?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.39,0:06:44.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They said I should be able to fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.20,0:06:44.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.98,0:06:47.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But how about Izuru...?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.60,0:06:49.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's do our best to \Nmake sure he doesn't
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.84,0:06:50.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,have to enter the fray!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.19,0:06:51.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.27,0:06:53.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll do my very bestest!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.69,0:06:54.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.16,0:07:01.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I feel as though they have
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.62,0:07:05.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,taught me that new lives grow \Nand develop on their own.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.62,0:07:10.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In that case, it is our job to do \Nall we can to protect those lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.38,0:07:15.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will personally participate \Nin this operation.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.47,0:07:18.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But-
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.63,0:07:20.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have made my mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.30,0:07:23.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We won't be using Red 5.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.08,0:07:23.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.35,0:07:26.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We can't reliably count \Non him in battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.52,0:07:29.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So please devise a plan \Nthat doesn't require him.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.73,0:07:31.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.52,0:07:36.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Losing Red 5 hurts, but I'll \Ncome up with something.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.44,0:07:39.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In exchange, Imperial Princess \NTeoria will be accompanying us.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.54,0:07:52.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Have you reached a decision?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.65,0:07:53.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.54,0:07:56.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see. Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.46,0:07:57.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As of right now, you are
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.88,0:07:59.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the Supreme Commander presiding \Nover this operation.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.22,0:08:03.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In exchange, I have a \Nfavor to ask of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.20,0:08:06.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There is something I'd like to use.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.31,0:08:10.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,With our next strike, we will \Nbring this shikaara to an end.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.69,0:08:13.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We shall overtake Earth in one bout and
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.81,0:08:17.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,seize the genes that \NKlein failed to obtain!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.07,0:08:19.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The final shikaara...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.07,0:08:21.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can hardly wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.45,0:08:26.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fight with all of your might...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.66,0:08:29.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...for our great ancestors \Nand descendants!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.63,0:08:39.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am bewildered by these lamata \Nwhom we refer to as "Earthlings".
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.88,0:08:40.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sir?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.80,0:08:43.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There are times when they prioritize
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.32,0:08:45.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the life of another over their own.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.68,0:08:49.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That is not the correct action \Nfor any living creature to take.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.48,0:08:52.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thinking back on the prior \Nspecies we've hunted,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.90,0:08:56.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the individual beings always \Nprioritized their own lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.23,0:08:57.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.15,0:09:03.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, we must hunt them down.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.06,0:09:07.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We have continued the shikaara in \Npursuit of increasingly advanced genes,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.87,0:09:13.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,believing that such measures will \Nhelp us survive in this universe...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.37,0:09:15.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that not so, Lumes?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.69,0:09:19.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir. That was what \Nthe oracle proclaimed.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.09,0:09:26.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Prince Jiart, the final \Nshikaara is about to begin.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.10,0:09:29.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Was this my brother's decision?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.06,0:09:29.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.52,0:09:32.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Have you heard word from Teoria?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.35,0:09:33.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing as of yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.69,0:09:35.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Either she has already passed away...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.89,0:09:39.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...or she has no desire to return to us.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.16,0:09:44.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Once this is over, we should be \Nable to find Princess Teoria.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.66,0:09:45.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,True enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.26,0:09:48.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Cheers to the shikaara!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.05,0:09:57.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I repeat: All civilians \Nresiding on Star Rose,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.73,0:10:00.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,please evacuate to Earth \Nwith all due haste.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.92,0:10:03.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I repeat: All civilians \Nresiding on Star Rose,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.42,0:10:06.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why does everyone suddenly \Nhave to leave Star Rose?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.68,0:10:08.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Probably 'cause it's dangerous up here.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.55,0:10:10.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Does that mean the enemy could \Nmake it this close to Earth?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.77,0:10:11.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's a possibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.71,0:10:15.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, guys! So this is where you went!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.48,0:10:19.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They're about to hold a general \Nbriefing for the upcoming operation!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.73,0:10:23.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Once that's over, you're \Nsupposed to board the Godinion.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.40,0:10:36.32,OS,,0000,0000,0000,,Great Chinese Alliance
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.32,0:10:40.24,OS,,0000,0000,0000,,Organization of the \NBela-Russian Conference
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.24,0:10:44.16,OS,,0000,0000,0000,,United Provinces of Africa
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.16,0:10:48.08,OS,,0000,0000,0000,,GDF General Headquarters
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.39,0:10:56.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now then, I am going to brief \Nyou on Operation: Heaven's Gate.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.88,0:11:00.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The primary goal of this operation \Nis to destroy the enemy's gate.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.27,0:11:05.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At a pre-determined time, all fleets \Nwill begin heading toward the gate.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.24,0:11:07.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We will instruct you on how to handle
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.67,0:11:09.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,any battles along the way as we see fit.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.87,0:11:12.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Upon reaching the gate, you are \Nto swiftly enter formation
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.62,0:11:14.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and prepare for the enemy to strike.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.83,0:11:17.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will explain the fleets' strategies \Nat a different point in time.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.33,0:11:21.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The MJP's Team Rabbits will \Nfight in the frontlines.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.13,0:11:23.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All armies are to offer \Ntheir full support.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.67,0:11:28.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All AHSMBs will be equipped \Nwith the markers needed
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.19,0:11:30.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,for when we fire the \NStraggle Laser at the gate.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.80,0:11:33.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Blue 1, Rose 3 and Black 6 will upset
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.72,0:11:36.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the enemy formation while \Nmoving toward the gate.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.04,0:11:38.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Gold 4 will offer support.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.56,0:11:40.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Purple 2 will issue \Norders from the rear.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.31,0:11:44.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The AHSMB units will take whatever \Nformation is necessary to
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.01,0:11:46.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,launch the markers, while all fleets \Nwill offer their full support.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.82,0:11:50.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As soon as they've launched the \Nmarkers, we will fire the Straggle Laser.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.82,0:11:51.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That is all.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.21,0:12:02.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you understand the \Noutline of the operation?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.46,0:12:03.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, ma'am!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.13,0:12:05.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We plow in and ka-boom!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.84,0:12:06.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Exactly.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.92,0:12:07.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.55,0:12:09.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What about me?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.47,0:12:11.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You'll remain on standby \Nwith us on the bridge.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.94,0:12:12.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Standby?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.80,0:12:13.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We aren't dispatching you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.83,0:12:15.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I feel fine!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.67,0:12:17.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Red 5!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.20,0:12:19.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Really, I wish I could leave \Nyou and your unit behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.89,0:12:23.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But there isn't room for \Nmistakes in this operation.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.27,0:12:27.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As such, there is a possibility that \NI may end up ordering you to sortie.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.53,0:12:29.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However, that is a last resort.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.03,0:12:31.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Understood?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.08,0:12:40.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't believe I'm stuck on standby...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.62,0:12:42.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm relieved.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.83,0:12:45.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now I don't have to worry about \Nyour health while I'm fighting.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.75,0:12:48.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You didn't have to put it like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.09,0:12:50.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That was cruel, Asagi.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.22,0:12:50.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.93,0:12:52.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But Asagi's absolutely right!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.80,0:12:56.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll do our best out there, \NIzuru, so cheer us on!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.18,0:12:59.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please leave this to us.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.02,0:13:01.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not you too, Ange!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.35,0:13:02.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.94,0:13:06.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In that case...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.86,0:13:08.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone, fight!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.49,0:13:11.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You literally cheered for us, sheesh...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.90,0:13:14.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Isn't that your pit crew, Asagi?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.47,0:13:15.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.82,0:13:17.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Asagi!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.03,0:13:17.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.08,0:13:20.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anna has gone missing!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.00,0:13:21.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's gone missing?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.54,0:13:23.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We can't bring her with us \Non this upcoming operation.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.79,0:13:26.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And since all civilians have been \Nordered to evacuate Star Rose,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.17,0:13:27.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,we tried to send her down to Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.17,0:13:30.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After she threw a tantrum \Nsaying she wouldn't go,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.34,0:13:31.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,she ran off somewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.72,0:13:34.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anna!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.99,0:13:37.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anna dear!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.30,0:13:39.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anna!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.37,0:13:41.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anna!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.05,0:13:43.74,OS,,0000,0000,0000,,The Shopping Arcade that Floats \Nin Space: Star Rose Galaxy
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.56,0:13:46.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She isn't here, is she?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.31,0:13:49.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This place is a total ghost town, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.90,0:13:51.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It seems rather forlorn, doesn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.03,0:13:54.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We can't find her after all of this.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.59,0:13:57.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I bet she must have \Ntaken the last pod down.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.67,0:14:02.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll check the list of passengers, so \Nplease make your way to the Godinion!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.58,0:14:06.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Asagi, do you have any idea \Nwhere she might have gone?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.82,0:14:14.96,OS,,0000,0000,0000,,Star Rose Galaxy Rest Area
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.01,0:14:17.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.35,0:14:21.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you think you're doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.10,0:14:26.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wanted one last ice cream cone.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.44,0:14:29.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on. We're going.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.82,0:14:30.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.52,0:14:31.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anna!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.48,0:14:34.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wanna stay with Papa and Grandpa!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.83,0:14:37.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if I went down to \NEarth, I'd be all alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.83,0:14:41.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You still can't come.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.74,0:14:42.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We can't take you with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.12,0:14:47.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your dad and grandpa don't \Nwant to put you in harm's way.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.79,0:14:51.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know how they feel.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.63,0:14:53.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is what it means to be family.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.38,0:14:57.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't want to see \Nhim get hurt, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.51,0:14:59.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My family, I mean.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.27,0:15:02.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder why...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.83,0:15:04.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's so strange!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.68,0:15:08.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We merely share the same DNA, \Nso why do I feel this way...?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.94,0:15:11.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Asagi, you have a family of your own?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.52,0:15:13.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I do.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.44,0:15:17.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When I heard that he wouldn't \Nbe participating in operation,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.17,0:15:20.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I felt relieved... big time.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.12,0:15:23.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.41,0:15:24.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Uh-huh.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.71,0:15:33.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Big Brother, fight!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.42,0:15:34.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fight!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.43,0:15:44.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Lady Teoria, I will protect you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.31,0:15:46.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please protect Izuru and \Nthe others instead of me.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.77,0:15:52.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why do we allow genetics to have \Nsuch a strong hold over us?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.19,0:15:56.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It feels as though we \Nare slaves to our genes.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.11,0:15:57.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Lady Teoria...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.07,0:16:02.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I cannot help but wonder, \N"Why was I drawn to Earth?"
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.62,0:16:05.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I believe that while humans \Nare slaves to their genes,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.94,0:16:08.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,they are also capable of \Nsurpassing their genetics.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.91,0:16:11.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Genetics are what connects families,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.46,0:16:14.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,clans and nations and \Nallows them to survive,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.69,0:16:17.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but occasionally people are able
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.33,0:16:20.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to protect others due to \N"love" and "friendship".
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.68,0:16:23.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That is true.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.38,0:16:28.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sometimes the humans defy their \Ngenetics and follow their hearts.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.36,0:16:33.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was worth abandoning the \NWulgaru simply to learn that.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.73,0:16:35.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I appreciate everything \Nyou've done, Daneel.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.90,0:16:40.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ninety-five percent of Star \NRose has been evacuated.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.57,0:16:42.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that right? Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.32,0:16:46.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why did we need to clear out Star Rose?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.45,0:16:48.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Supreme Commander issued that order.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.37,0:16:49.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Supreme Commander?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.02,0:16:51.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not the GDF's Commander-in-Chief?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.69,0:16:55.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right. He is finally making his move.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.38,0:17:01.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They said that this is the \Nlast pod going down to Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.18,0:17:02.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm glad we made it in time!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.97,0:17:05.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. Anna's dad and \Ngrandpa were able to
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.39,0:17:07.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,put their minds at ease \Nand return to the Pit.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.39,0:17:10.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now we can finally head \Non out to the Godinion!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.23,0:17:12.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yep! Please hurry on over!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.06,0:17:16.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Asagi!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.78,0:17:17.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, kid!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.98,0:17:19.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What were you thinking?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.32,0:17:20.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going with you after all!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.65,0:17:21.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.99,0:17:24.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How am I supposed to \Nexplain this to your dad?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.91,0:17:26.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going anyway!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.13,0:17:26.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.37,0:17:31.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't... want to wait...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.16,0:17:34.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,alone on Earth worrying about everyone!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.55,0:17:40.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You win.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.17,0:17:44.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But let's beat those Wulgaru!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.22,0:17:45.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.94,0:17:59.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.28,0:18:04.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,C'mon! We're down to the last lap!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.24,0:18:05.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's give it all we've got!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.53,0:18:09.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Miss, we have her running \Nperfectly for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.20,0:18:10.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.74,0:18:13.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Um... I made this for you!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.87,0:18:14.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's eat it together...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.87,0:18:15.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.96,0:18:17.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a cake...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.42,0:18:18.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is it edible?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.96,0:18:21.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It might be a bit sweet.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.21,0:18:23.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All right. We'll give it a try.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.93,0:18:25.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Too sweet!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.73,0:18:27.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is awful!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.39,0:18:30.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll teach you how to bake a \Ncake once this mission is over.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.22,0:18:33.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll kick their butts, \Nso lend me a hand!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.60,0:18:37.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're welcome to call us "Bro"!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.95,0:18:39.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.03,0:18:41.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We heard that you're \Nlookin' for a big brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.07,0:18:43.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nah, I'm cool...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.90,0:18:44.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's hear it!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.99,0:18:46.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Say it nice and loud!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.14,0:18:48.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I'll pass! I don't \Nneed any brothers!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.45,0:18:56.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I need to watch what I say \Nwhen I'm piloting you...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.48,0:18:59.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Otherwise all of Earth \Nwill hear my potty mouth.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.21,0:19:02.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You locked it?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.46,0:19:03.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry 'bout that!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.56,0:19:05.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I heard those were Captain \NSuzukaze's orders.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.98,0:19:08.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That way you won't take off \Nwithout permission, Izuru.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.60,0:19:10.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But maintenance-wise, it's good to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.06,0:19:15.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone, all of the fleets \Nwill be launching soon!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.39,0:19:19.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Izuru, please go to the bridge.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.40,0:19:20.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.70,0:19:21.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You are on standby.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.32,0:19:24.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Izuru...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.82,0:19:29.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You weren't born for the \Nsole purpose to fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.32,0:19:32.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The way Rin-Rin locked Red 5 shows \Nthat she feels the same way I do.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.25,0:19:37.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The designated time for \Nlaunch will be in 12 hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.76,0:19:45.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kei?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.72,0:19:47.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is something the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.05,0:19:51.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If it's about Izuru, he'll be fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.01,0:19:55.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll make sure he doesn't get sent out.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.89,0:19:57.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Asagi...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.06,0:19:58.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll do my best to make sure \Nhe doesn't have to fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.94,0:20:00.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can count us in on that, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.72,0:20:02.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All of us will do our best out there!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.82,0:20:04.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will do the very best I possibly can.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.98,0:20:05.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ange...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.94,0:20:07.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm counting on you, Ange.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.82,0:20:08.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.86,0:20:11.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Guys, we've got to strive \Nto become heroes!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.24,0:20:13.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And amazing enough to make \NIzuru green with envy!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.58,0:20:14.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Asagi,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.57,0:20:16.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,don't push yourself too hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.21,0:20:18.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.83,0:20:20.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Make sure to take some antacids.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.25,0:20:23.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Actually, I don't need antacids anymore!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.85,0:20:26.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You still have the residual \Nairs of a failure...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.05,0:20:27.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,True enough!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.15,0:20:28.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Seriously!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.76,0:20:31.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.61,0:20:44.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Informing all fleets:
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.61,0:20:47.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am hereby transferring \Nall authority of command
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.57,0:20:49.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,over the current operation \Nto the following individual,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.82,0:20:52.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Simon Gato of the MJP.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.70,0:20:55.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am Simon Gato.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.44,0:20:59.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will be issuing all \Ncommands from the Star Rose.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.21,0:21:02.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Star Rose?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.88,0:21:05.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Operation: Heaven's Gate, activate!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.88,0:21:07.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Cables, purge!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.91,0:21:12.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Star Rose will carry \Nall of the fleets' ships!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.77,0:21:26.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Captain Amane, it's from \NSupreme Commander Simon.
